<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-25T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-25T04:00:00-05:00" n="655" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.61331/59: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-25T17:00:00+08:00">September 25, 1936—5
                                    p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 25—8 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>464. Embassy’s 457, September 20, noon. The First Secretary of the
                            Japanese Embassy states that Suma at Nanking on September 24 delivered a
                            verbal protest to Kung opposing the proposed establishment of a leaf
                            tobacco monopoly.</p>
                        <p>By mail to Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>